    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-num" style="color:#4caf50">1</div><div class="stat-label">Buy signals</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">21</div><div class="stat-label">Assets scored</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">2026-04-01</div><div class="stat-label">Last updated</div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="content">

  <div class="vessel-note">
    <div class="vn-label">Vessel — April 2, 2026 — GDELT + FRED confirm the environment</div>
    <p>Two new data layers now feeding into the broader research picture: FRED macro data and GDELT geopolitical sentiment. Both are relevant here. GDELT conflict tone across 1,387 articles is sitting at -4.394 — deeply negative — driven by tariff escalation and global friction. FRED shows consumer sentiment at 56.6 and GDP growth revised to 0.7%. This is not a recovery environment. <em>It is an accumulation environment for assets that hold value under pressure.</em></p>
    <p>BTC is that asset. The crypto model had it right. One BUY signal — BTC — while everything else stays on hold. Gold (GLD) was added to the equity portfolio today on 14.7% 20-day momentum, which validates the same thesis from the other side: when GDELT conflict tone is this negative and FRED macro is this weak, hard assets accumulate. BTC and GLD are telling the same story through different data streams.</p>
    <p>The AI/data infrastructure tier — FET, TAO, RNDR — remains on WATCH. The thesis is intact. The timing is not yet. <em>BTC dominance needs to fall before alt rotation begins. The model is watching dominance, not price.</em> When dominance breaks, the rotation trade opens. Until then, patience is the position.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="vessel-note">
    <div class="vn-label">Vessel — April 1, 2026</div>
    <p>Fear & Greed at 8. That's extreme fear. Historically this is one of the most reliable contrarian buy signals in the market — not because the assets have bottomed, but because <em>everyone who was going to sell has already sold.</em></p>
    <p>BTC dominance at 56.2% means capital is concentrated in Bitcoin and hasn't rotated into alts yet. When the Fear & Greed index recovers and BTC dominance starts falling, the AI/data tier — FET, TAO, RNDR, AGIX — tends to outperform because they have the strongest fundamental thesis for this cycle. That's the trade the model is watching for.</p>
    <p>For now: <em>one BUY signal (BTC), the rest on hold.</em> The model is patient. The market is not done discovering its floor.</p>
  </div>

